This paper deals with the VC-dimensions of nondeterministic finite automata, which is a topic in formal language theory (FL). The paper also involves combinatorial and algorithmic aspects, which could fall under the categories of data structures (DS), computational complexity (CC), and discrete mathematics (LO). Finally, the paper uses information theory (IT) techniques to obtain its results.
